>Yes, I'm having troubles compiling NEAT.  I am on a windows
>system, and would like some help in getting all the correct packages
>and version etc. in order to compile and run the NEAT experiments.

I have a working version of the NEAT source which will compile under Cygwin
using an ordinary make, if you'd like me to send it to you. I think you just
need to get hold of the latest SWIG. (The usual Cygwin setup program will
handle this for you.) I have, however, removed all of the graphics code,
simply because I didn't really need it and it just simplified the porting
process. If you do need NEAT's graphics output, you'll have to sort that out
yourself.

--Darren
